    <p>
        THERE WAS A CONFLICT BETWEEN THE APOSTOLIC CHURCH IN GHANA  AND PASTOR JAMES MCKEOWN.SO TO RESOLVE 
        THE CONFLICT THE THEN PRESIDENT OF GHANA, 
        DR KWAME NKRUMAH RULED THAT THE CHURCH ADOPTED A NEW NAME THUS IN AUGUST 1962 THE NAME CHURCH OF 
        PENTECOST CAME INTO BEING.THE CHURCH STARTED BY PASTOR JAMES MCKEOWN STARTED 
        WITH A FEW PEOPLE OF WHICH MOST OF THEM WERE WOMEN.
    </p> 

 <div>
    <p>
        THE CHURCH STARTED FROM ASAMANKESE WITH THE HELP 
        OF SOME BELIEVERS OF THE APOSTOLIC FAITH AND NOW HAS ABOUT 5MILLIONS  BELIEVERS AND CAN BE LOCATED 
        IN ABOUT 109 OUT OF 195 COUNTRIES IN THE WORLD.
    </p>
    <img src="images/enterance.png.jpg">
</div>
    
